<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="65" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.00101/66</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Minutes of the Daily Meetings of the Commissioners
                            Plenipotentiary, Thursday, May 8th, 1919</hi></head>
                    <dateline>
                        <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-08">May 8, 1919</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <list type="participants">
                        <item>Present: <list>
                                <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Lansing</hi></item>
                                <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. White</hi></item>
                                <item><hi rend="smallcaps">General Bliss</hi></item>
                                <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Herter</hi></item>
                            </list></item>
                    </list>
                    <pb facs="0213" n="177" xml:id="pg_177"/>
                    <p>1. Memorandum No. 266 addressed to General Bliss regarding dinner to the
                        Foreign Representatives on the Joint Secretariat written by Colonel U. S.
                        Grant was considered by the Commissioners. They decided that it would be
                        most desirable for Colonel Grant to give the dinner which he suggests and
                        left the question of expenses to his discretion. <seg type="margin">Dinner
                            to Joint Secretariat by Col. Grant</seg></p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>